The discovery of a fertilefemale Mediterranean fruit fly in a backyard apple tree maylead to aerial spraying in Orange County, California StateDepartment of Agriculture officials said.    California Department of Agriculture spokeswoman Gera Currysaid more than 1,700 traps have been set in an 80-square milearea around the Westminster neighborhood following thediscovery. The fly was found in a trap routinely checked byagriculture officials.    Curry said if aerial spraying is used, it would be one-timespray, unlike the nightly sprayings used in 1980. Reuter&#3;